==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hornbeam
<hw>Horn"beam`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Beam</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tree of the genus
<gen>Carpinus</gen> (<spn>Carpinus Americana</spn>), having a smooth
gray bark and a ridged trunk, the wood being white and very hard. It is
common along the banks of streams in the United States, and is also
called <altname>ironwood</altname>. The English hornbeam is
<spn>Carpinus Betulus</spn>. The American is called also <altname>blue
beech</altname> and <altname>water beech</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hop hornbeam</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Hop</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornbill</ent>⟦br⟧
